.NET Framework 3.5.name: OVRTracker
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: An infrared camera that tracks the position of a head-mounted display.

methods.name: GetPose(int tracker)
methods.summary: Gets the sensor's pose, relative to the head's pose at the time of the last pose recentering.

methods.name: GetPoseValid(int tracker)
methods.summary: If true, the pose of the sensor is valid and is ready to be queried.

properties.name: count
properties.summary: Returns the number of sensors currently connected to the system.

properties.name: isEnabled
properties.summary: If this is true and a sensor is available, the system will use position tracking when isPositionTracked is also true.

properties.name: isPositionTracked
properties.summary: If true, the sensor is actively tracking the HMD's position. Otherwise the HMD may be temporarily occluded, the system may not support position tracking, etc.

properties.name: isPresent
properties.summary: If true, a sensor is attached to the system.
